.TH "snd_dmaengine_pcm_refine_runtime_hwparams" 9 "snd_dmaengine_pcm_refine_runtime_hwparams" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_dmaengine_pcm_refine_runtime_hwparams \- Refine runtime hw params
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_dmaengine_pcm_refine_runtime_hwparams
.BI "(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream "  ","
.BI "struct snd_dmaengine_dai_dma_data *dma_data "  ","
.BI "struct snd_pcm_hardware *hw "  ","
.BI "struct dma_chan *chan "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "substream" 12
PCM substream
.IP "dma_data" 12
DAI DMA data
.IP "hw" 12
PCM hw params
.IP "chan" 12
DMA channel to use for data transfers
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 on success, a negative error code otherwise.

This function will query DMA capability, then refine the pcm hardware
parameters.
